{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_lima_ver02/data/sn83045433/100493305/1910061101/0161.xml":{"full_text":"THE WASHINGTON HERALD, SATURDAY, JURE 11, 1910. 11\nWALL STREET NEWS\nPoor Copper Report Causes\nBreak of Four Points.\nShares\nShares\nOTHER STOCKS ON DECLINE\nNo Great Amount of Real Liguida\ntion Marks Transactions of the\nDay, Close of Which Experiences\na Slight Rally=Chicage and Alion\nShares Also Unsettling Factor,\n\nNew York, June 10.~With the specula\ntive interests for the fall largely eiimin\nated from the market values stocks to\nday were quickly susceptible to the ex\ntreme weakness that developed in such\nan active stock as Amalgamated Copper.\nPressure was continually brought to bear\nagainst this issue from the very begin\nning of business and kept up until the\nend of the day. It caused an extreme\nbreak of 43-8 points in the price of the\nstock from which a slight rally was\nmade just before the close,\n\nThe ostensible reason for this was, of\ncourse, the poor report of the copper\nproducers association made public the\nday before yesterday which exhibited an\nincrease in the accumulated surplus of\ncopper metal during the month, of 18,\n441,000 pounds.\nProduction in ixcess,\nA fair commentary upon the copper\nsituation is that the so-called insiders\ndid not have to walt until to-day to be\ncome convinced that current copper pro\nduction in the country was running In\nexcess of consumption and the selling of\nAmalgamated Copper shares to-day was of\nsort that plainly suggested the renewal of\n\u201cpear\u201d operations in the stock.\n\nAt the same time the copper situation\nis undoubtedly unfavorable, and the pre\nsumption seems fair that it will continue\nto be unfavorable until some sort of re\nstriction of copper production takes place\nOn the other hand, such restriction near\nly always has taken place under suck\ncircumstances as the present, and to\nday's break in Amalgamated Copper may\nperhaps, be an indication of the fact thal\na movement toward a partial shut dowr\nof some of the country\u2019s largest coppe\nproducing mines such as that which oc\ncurred within the last twelve months\nmay be near at hand.\n\nAgain to-day an unsettling factor I\nthe stock market was a sharp decline In\nthe highly Inactive Chicage and Alto:\ncommon shares which, considering the\npresent price of the stock, inevitably les\nto an impression that the continuance\ndividend distributions upon the issue a\nleast at the present rate was more oO\nless uncertain.\nSuch an Event Possible.\nBut for that matter the market valua\ntion of Alton commen shares has for\nlong time back suggested that such a\nevent was among the strong probabili\nties, The annual report of the Alton, pub\nlishe\u00e9 a long time since, for the fisca\nyear ended June 30, last year, showe\nonly a trifling surplus over the 4 per cen\ndividend paid on the common shares\nA sharp fall also occurred in Toledc\nSt. Louis and Western stock, which own\na very considerable quantity of the Alto:\nshares. Declines In the leading stock\nto-day apart from Amalgamated Coppe\nwere generally from one to two points\nbut they were accompanied by no lars\nincrease in the volume of trading, no\ndid they seem to be attended with an\nconsiderable amount of real liquidation\n\n\n\n\n\nQuotations furnished by W. B. Hibbs Co,, mem\nbers of the New York\nbers of the New York Stock Exchange, Hibbs Build\ning. Bid, Asked.\nEIR ar SS wi- B\nBritish Columbia Copper....c.ceeee. 5% 52\nButte Coalition.........cccevene sxsaves 3B 18%\nChicago Subway.........coce.s PANIES 2%\nCobalt a MM 18\nEly Central....... paesisssvsesssveins 118 TR\nGiroux Copper... RT RA TIN EL 6% Te\nGoldfield Ceonsolidated..... sassesranss 58 812-16\nBorr JARE..........vtisescrsivsrncninne A 85\nManhattan Trensit........coeeeee wees 150 i%\nTr, RL RCE Sp APY. caere\u2014 19 19%\nMines of America....... 8\nNevada-Utah M. 8. Corpoveeee.. 1316\nNipissing Mines Company....... ees 34 nx\nOhio  Coppar......coressan